      "descriptions": [
        "The ELIXIR Beacon Network (EBN) is a federated discovery platform that allows users to query distributed biomedical datasets (such as genomic and phenotypic data) through the GA4GH Beacon v2 protocol. Rather than centralising data, the service queries participating Beacons real time and returns aggregated results while preserving local data sovereignty. EBN brings value by facilitating standardized, privacy-preserving data discovery in a federated manner. It supports a seamless integration of Node-operated Beacon servers and establishes a unified search layer for European biomedical data infrastructures. Developed under ELIXIR, the network creates an interconnected ecosystem of beacons, fostering responsible sharing of genomic, phenotypic and other data types. <br/> The onboarding of new Beacons is regulated by standardized governance and validation procedures. The service includes Beacon registration, validation and monitoring, public web interface and API for federated search and governance structure for decision-making. As EBN serves purely as a data discovery service, it does not entail storage of raw or individual-level data, data access management nor brokering, and neither bioinformatic analysis or compute services."
      ],
